  "name": "Nagaraja COU1 — Non-cannulated pedicle screw compression-bending credibility assessment (Minimal profile)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for FEA prediction of ASTM F1717 static compression-bending performance of a non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct. The FEA model ensemble (FDA, Ansys, DePuy Synthes) is compared against N=11 experimental constructs across two laboratories. All 13 V&V 40 factors assessed; one factor (Test conditions) is below required level due to a single test condition being evaluated. The intended use is confined to static compression-bending loading in an ASTM F1717 bench-test configuration for a Class II non-cannulated pedicle screw; the model is not intended for in vivo fatigue or dynamic loading predictions. This scope is fully described in the Claim and Requirement nodes bound below.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/req/f1717-static-compression-bending-v1",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/claim/fea-predicts-f1717-construct-stiffness-and-yield",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/model/pedicle-screw-fea-ensemble-v2",
