      "rationale": "All FEA software (Ansys Mechanical 2021 R2) is under configuration management with documented version control, regression testing, and an audit trail. SQA procedures conform to FDA software lifecycle guidance and ASME V&V 10 recommendations."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for the declared model risk level.",
      "rationale": "Benchmark problems with known analytical solutions (beam bending, contact patch) were solved to confirm correct solver implementation. Results matched analytical references within 0.5%."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for the declared model risk level.",
      "rationale": "A systematic mesh convergence study was conducted using three mesh densities. The Richardson extrapolation-based GCI for construct stiffness was below 2.1%, satisfying the required discretization error threshold."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
