      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for the declared model risk level.",
      "rationale": "N=11 test constructs were assembled from production-intent 7.5 mm non-cannulated pedicle screws and UHMWPE test blocks. Sample selection followed a stratified scheme to cover the geometric tolerance range of the screw lot."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for the declared model risk level.",
      "rationale": "Testing was performed at a single load angle (5°) per ASTM F1717. Variation across multiple load angles was not explored, limiting the breadth of validation conditions. This factor is below the required level and represents a documented gap in the credibility evidence."
